    </svg>
  </div>
  <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-xs text-center text-gray-500">Standard Indian/IEC positive phase sequence: R leads Y by 120°, Y leads B by 120°. Reversed (negative) sequence: R-B-Y.</div>
</div>

<p>If any two phases are swapped — say, the R and Y connections are interchanged — the motor sees the sequence R-B-Y instead of R-Y-B. The rotating magnetic field in the stator reverses direction, and the motor turns in the opposite direction. All three-phase motors are affected the same way: swap any two phases, reverse the direction of rotation.</p>

<h2 id="consequences">Consequences of Wrong Phase Sequence</h2>

<div class="my-6 space-y-2">
  {[
    { icon: '⚙️', equip: 'Three-phase induction motors', consequence: 'Reverses rotation. May trip on overload immediately (pump against closed valve, compressor at wrong end), or operate at reduced efficiency.' },
    { icon: '🏗️', equip: 'Overhead cranes and hoists', consequence: 'Reversal of lift direction. A load commanded to raise may lower. Extremely dangerous — potential for serious injury or fatality.' },
    { icon: '💧', equip: 'Centrifugal pumps', consequence: 'Reversed impeller rotation. Pump will not develop head or flow. Prolonged reverse running can damage mechanical seals and bearings.' },
    { icon: '❄️', equip: 'Compressors (reciprocating/screw)', consequence: 'Incorrect valve sequence. Reduced output. Potential mechanical damage to valve seats and suction/discharge arrangement.' },
    { icon: '🔌', equip: 'Transformers and switchgear', consequence: 'Phase sequence affects power quality instruments and directional protection relays. Incorrect sequence can cause protection maloperation.' },
    { icon: '📊', equip: 'Energy meters (three-phase)', consequence: 'Some older induction disc meters run backwards on reverse phase sequence — resulting in negative energy registration.' },
  ].map(item => (
    <div class="flex gap-3 p-4 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl">
      <span class="text-xl shrink-0">{item.icon}</span>
      <div>
        <div class="font-bold text-red-900 text-sm">{item.equip}</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-red-800 mt-0.5">{item.consequence}</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

<Callout type="warning" title="Never start a motor without checking phase sequence first">
  On any new installation, after any wiring modification, after a switchgear replacement, or after any work that involves disturbing cable connections — always check phase sequence before energising three-phase motors. The thirty seconds it takes is insignificant compared to the cost of a seized compressor or a crane accident.
</Callout>

<h2 id="how-to-test">How to Test Phase Sequence</h2>

<p>The simplest and most reliable method is a dedicated phase sequence indicator (also called a phase rotation tester). These instruments connect to the three-phase supply via three test leads and immediately display whether the sequence is correct (positive, R-Y-B) or reversed (negative, R-B-Y).</p>

<div class="my-6 space-y-2">
  {[
    { step: 'Identify the phase conductors', detail: 'In Indian installations, R is red, Y is yellow, B is blue, N is black. In new IEC colour-coded installations: L1 brown, L2 black, L3 grey.' },
    { step: 'Connect the phase sequence indicator', detail: 'Clip or probe R/L1 to the R terminal of the PSI, Y/L2 to Y, B/L3 to B. The instrument typically has colour-coded probes or terminals.' },
    { step: 'Energise (or the supply is already live)', detail: 'Phase sequence indicators are designed for live measurement — this is a voltage measurement, not current.' },
    { step: 'Read the display', detail: 'A rotating disc indicator spins clockwise for correct RYB sequence, anticlockwise for reversed. LED indicators light green for correct, red for reversed. Digital instruments show "RYB" or "RBY" (or equivalent).' },
    { step: 'Correct if reversed', detail: 'To reverse sequence, swap any two of the three phase conductors at the motor terminal box or at the supply incomer. Retest after swapping.' },
  ].map((s, i) => (
    <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
      <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-[#E0252E] flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-xs mt-0.5">{i + 1}</div>
      <div class="pb-2 border-b border-gray-100 flex-1">
        <div class="font-semibold text-[#0D1B2A] text-sm">{s.step}</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-0.5">{s.detail}</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

<h2 id="visual-indicator">Types of Phase Sequence Indicators</h2>

<div class="my-6 grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
  {[
    { type: 'Rotating disc', desc: 'Traditional design with a small induction motor. Clockwise rotation = correct. Reliable, no batteries required. Robust for field use.', models: 'CIE PSI-1' },
    { type: 'LED indicator', desc: 'Modern design — lights green for correct sequence, red for reversed. Compact, fast. Some models also display individual phase voltage levels.', models: 'CIE PSI-2' },
    { type: 'Digital multifunction', desc: 'Displays phase sequence, individual phase voltages, frequency, and phase-to-phase voltage. Ideal for commissioning and site surveys.', models: 'CIE-5050A' },
  ].map(item => (
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
      <div class="font-bold text-[#0D1B2A] text-sm mb-1">{item.type}</div>
